Q.9 --> How is Cell Padding different from Cell Spacing? With Example.

Ans:- 
      
    -->  Cell Padding:

      1. Cell Padding controls the space between the content of a table cell and the cell's inner boundaries.
      2. It determines how much space there should be between the content and the cell's borders.
      
      Example:
        <!-- Add Cellpadding --> 
        <table border="1" cellpadding="5" >

            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>#id</th>
                    <th>Name</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
                <tr align="center">
                    <td>1</td>
                    <td>UTSAV</td>
                </tr> 
            </tfoot>

        </table>


    -->  Cell Spacing: 

      1. Cell spacing is the space between each cell.
      2. It determines how much space should be added between the borders of cells.

      Example: 
        <!-- Add Cellspacing -->
        <table border="1" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="5">

            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>#id</th>
                    <th>Name</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
                <tr align="center">
                    <td>1</td>
                    <td>UTSAV</td>
                </tr> 
            </tfoot>

        </table>

